It’s incredibly sad to see that THIS is what it has come to. Yesterday morning we witnessed this majestic rhino sadly getting dehorned. It was emotional and distressing.

Back in 2015, 850 rhinos were killed for their horns. So to save it from being poached, it’s come down to going through this very process which is the last resort to help them.

This rhino has been darted from above which takes approximately 6-7 mins to get knocked out. Once it’s safe to do so, the professionals step in to cover it’s eyes, cool it down, treat it for ticks, take bloods & a feces sample is also taken for testing. 

A chainsaw is then used to remove the horn which is technically painless but we cannot underestimate how sad & how traumatic this is for the innocent creatures. 

To remove something it uses everyday isn’t ideal but it seems to be making a difference. We don’t want them to be part of history so to prevent them from extinction, there are currently 21 players on tour who raise funds with every birdie made.

It’s no small task to make a big difference but hats off to @justinjwalters & @burmygolf for starting up the @birdies4rhinos foundation, every little helps! 

#BirdiesForRhinos #SaveRhinos #Dehorning #PreventExtinction #LastResort

@james_robinson_golf, @dannymaude & I unexpectedly played “Cat & Mouse” at the @callawaygolf HQ in LA. The rules are very simple, bookmark this game and give it a go at some point! 

Rules:
You need double the number of balls there are players. So for instance, if there are 3 players, you need six balls. Alternatively, if 8 of you are taking part, you need 16 balls. 

Collectively, agree on a footage. In this case, we made them 5ft putts. Making it a challenging yet holeable distance is the most fun in my opinion 🥳

Before you begin, make sure everyone is at their stations which has got to be every other ball. In other words, there should be a ball in between each player. 

It doesn’t matter where you start but if you hole it, you move on (clockwise). However if you miss it, you stay put at the same putt. 

If you’re overtaken, you’re out including the ball opposite the player. So every time a player goes out, so is the ball he or she has missed and the one opposite meaning the player and two balls are eliminated.

Give it a go & tag us to show us your best efforts, good luck! 🤣

We had such a fantastic day at @thegrovehotel and I couldn’t think of a better way to celebrate my father in law’s 60th 😎 It’s only 25 mins down the road for us and it’s honestly heaven on earth! 

Interestingly, it’s not a members club so it feels like a real treat every time we get to play here! From the quality of golf course, the facility and the top tier service, I’ll never get bored of it!

One of the main defenses here at Walton Heath for the @aigwomensopen is the HEATHER! This time of year, the “ling” strands not only pop in colour due to them flowering but they’re also not as pretty to play out of as they look! You want to avoid it at all costs! 

Here’s my first then second attempt coming out of them! 

Thanks @adidasgolf for the invite to play in the Pro-Am, despite the weather, we all still had a blast! 🙌🏽

With summer finally here, and the AIG Women’s British Open in full swing at Walton Heath, there is no better time to get into golf (or to carry on your golfing journey).

So, whether it’s on the course, on the range, or at a wonderful indoor facility like @pitchgolf, Callaway and Big Bertha REVA will be there to help you enjoy it and get the most out of your game.

#Callaway | #WomensSport | #WomensGolf

Dunhill links - Day 5, round 3 ☔️

This was my personal highlight of the day… 🤣 Today we filmed a video for my YouTube channel on how to plan a golf trip because it’s diffferent for everyone but often you don’t know where to start. For me, the golf is important and @qdlresort is always an enjoyable venue to play but it offers so much more. I had my first ever paddle tennis lesson at @thecampusqdl  which is an unreal set up (I can’t wait to explore it further tomorrow) and I have a boarder line new obsession for the sport plus we ate at two incredible spots which I couldn’t recommend enough. @casadolagoqdl & @bovinosteakhouse 🔥 Whether you like seafood or meat, Quinta has you covered!

Some may say I’m giving off Rafa vibes, others may describe it as a work of art or nearing perfection 🤣 I absolutely loved our time at @thecampusqdl within the @qdlresort, I can’t wait to share with you what we got up to here! 

Ps, It was my first go at tennis, I’m already buzzing to get kitted up in all the gear 🎾

Tag someone who needs help with their chipping 😅

Earlier this year we were at @golfatthegrove celebrating a family outing and I stumbled across this station already set up in the short game area! With that being said, I thought I’d make the most of it during my warm up and it really helped me during my round unsurprisingly! 

I hope you find this video somewhat useful so next time you’re warming up, use balls, tee’s or markers to replace the disc’s I was using (because who in their right mind casually Carrie’s around discs already in their golf bag 😂) and go through this drill to calibrate your feel & visualisation. 

You’re much better off doing something like this than mindlessly hitting balls for the sake of it, enjoy! ⛳️ 

Ps, Don’t forget to bookmark this in case you can’t remember how to set it up and execute next time you have the chance to 🥳
